      "content": "I strongly advise against giving your child adult aspirin to break a fever. Adult and children's aspirin have different dosages for various reasons. Using the adult dose can lead to serious side effects in children, including Reye's syndrome and St. Vitus' dance. Please consider visiting an urgent care center or a 24-hour pharmacy that can provide guidance on medication usage for children or taking your child to the ER for immediate evaluation and care.",
